# Revert Vertical Layout & Restore Ambient Mode (Phase 12+)

Reverting the "vertical-all" layout bug while implementing a high-fidelity, YouTube-style "Ambient Mode" that samples video colors in real-time.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Layout Revert**: Long-form videos will return to their natural horizontal (16:9) flow, while Shorts will maintain their vertical (9:16) optimization.
>
> **Ambient Mode**: I will implement a canvas-based sampler that creates a dynamic, glowing background around the video player, matching the video's colors in real-time.

## Proposed Changes

### Video Component
#### [MODIFY] [VideoPlayer.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoPlayer.tsx)
- Add `isShort` prop to handle aspect ratio.
- If `!isShort`, use `aspect-video` (16:9).
- If `isShort`, use `aspect-[9/16]` (9:16) on mobile/desktop appropriately.
- Refine **Ambient Mode**:
    - Improve canvas sampling logic.
    - Add a smoother blur and saturation to the background glow.
    - Ensure it fits the video dimensions regardless of orientation.

### Watch Feature
#### [MODIFY] [WatchClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/watch/[id]/WatchClient.tsx)
- Pass `is_short` from the video data to the [VideoPlayer](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoPlayer.tsx#24-356).
- Adjust the layout container to handle vertical videos gracefully in the horizontal "Watch" page (centered with black bars/ambient glow).

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Subagent Tests
- Navigate to a horizontal video: Verify 16:9 layout and ambient glow.
- Navigate to a Short: Verify 9:16 layout (vertical) and ambient glow.
- Click play/pause: Verify Ambient Mode stops/starts.

### Manual Verification
- Resize browser: Ensure horizontal videos don't stretch vertically.
- Verify "Ambient Mode" toggle in settings menu works.
